name: Darren EADES, Petitioner v. PHILADELPHIA COMMON PLEAS COURTS, Respondent
name_abbreviation: Eades v. Philadelphia Common Pleas Courts

parties: Darren EADES, Petitioner v. PHILADELPHIA COMMON PLEAS COURTS, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM
AND NOW, this 5th day of October, 2015, the Application for Leave to File Original Process and the Petition for Writ of Mandamus and/or Extraordinary Relief, to the extent it seeks mandamus relief, are GRANTED. The court of common pleas is DIRECTED to dispose of the pending habeas corpus filing within 90 days.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM
